On Thu, 24 Jul 2003, Rob Carpenter wrote:

> I dont want to slam it just make it more of an even
> height with the rear, i dont like the low-rider look..

Buses normally sit a bit front-high when parked.  That is because when the
driver gets in it pushes the front end down level with the back, if the
back is properly adjusted.  If your bus isn't level with a person in the
driver's seat, then you need to adjust the rear torsion bars, not the
front.

George Lyle
